<DOCNO> XIE19970218.0002 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-17 16:54 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tehran's District Mayor Imprisoned for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, February 17 (Xinhua) -- An Iranian court condemned a
district mayor in the capital of Tehran to 13 years imprisonment
for receiving bribes equivalent to 11,300 U.S. dollars, local
press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Mozaffar Nafari, former mayor of district 6 in Tehran, might
be the first victim of high-ranking government officials in the
nationwide move against the ever worsening corruption in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The court has ordered that Nafari would pay back the private
companies and pay the equivalent in fines to the court system.
</P>
<P>
The court also found the former mayor guilty of unlawfully
providing his second wife with a car and apartment which
belonged to the municipality.
</P>
<P>
The court decreed that the mayor would receive 91 lashes and
would be sent "exile" to the Iranian southeastern city of
Zahedan, a city known for its harsh climate, for having an
affairs with a woman whose identity has been withheld.
</P>
<P>
Iranian laws, derived from Islamic laws, forbid men and women
to have extramarital sexual relations. Depending on the
circumstances of the violation, violators could receive lashes
or other punishment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
