<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 3 Men Hanged for Homicide in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, February 17 (Xinhua) -- Three Iranians were hanged in
the open yard of a prison in central Tehran today on charge of
murders, according to a source at the prison.
</P>
<P>
Hossein Darvish, 36, Hassan Rahmani, 40, and Hamid Kouhi, 28,
were put to death by hanging in the Qasre Prison because they
failed to get a reprieve from Iran's supreme court, the source
said.
</P>
<P>
They had been charged with and confessed to different
murders. The Islamic procedure of Qisas (Retribution) requires
that killers be put to death unless immediate family members
forgive the killer.
</P>
<P>
However, the families of the victims refused to offer
forgiveness and they were present at the prison to witness the
hanging. 
</P>
</TEXT>
