<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Six People Killed in U.S. Helicopter, Plane Crashes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 17 (Xinhua) -- Six people were killed and
another injured in air crashes of a small plane and a helicopter
in two days in the United States.
</P>
<P>
A sheriff's helicopter lost power and crashed near San Diego
Sunday evening, killing a deputy and inured the pilot.
</P>
<P>
The Hughes 500 helicopter, investigating suspected trespassers,
went down on private property near Santee Lakes, a rural area
about 20 miles northeast of downtown San Diego.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Pat Coyle, 42, was critically wounded and died about
three hours later. The pilot, Ron Hobson, was hospitalized in
stable condition.
</P>
<P>
On Friday night, a single-engine plane crashed in New Mexico,
killing five people in their 20s and late teens.
</P>
<P>
The two man and three women were returning to Albuquerque
following dinner when the plane went down moments after taking off
from an airport 30 miles (50 km) south of the Colorado state
line. 
</P>
</TEXT>
