<HEADLINE> Ukraine to Increase Outdoor Ad Prices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, February 17 (Xinhua) -- Outdoor advertisement prices for
foreign companies or products are expected to have a five-fold
increase when a new law is at place at the end of this month.
</P>
<P>
"The new tariffs will be approved by the end of February,"
Stanisla Stashevsky, deputy mayor of Kiev, said today.
</P>
<P>
More than half of all open-air ads will likely be affected by
the change, he said.
</P>
<P>
City officials said Kiev, the capital of Ukraine, is losing
much-needed ad revenues due to widespread piracy.
</P>
<P>
"Although Kiev tariffs for billboards match European norms, the
city has not received substantial amounts of this money," said
Yevhen Zyryansky, head of the city advertising department.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that Kiev received only 1 million U.S. dollars in
revenues from outdoor ads last year.
</P>
<P>
However, representatives of several ad agencies alleged that
increased tariffs will lead to more advertising piracy.
</P>
<P>
Presently, the cost of an outdoor billboard rangs from 150 to
1,000 dollars per month in the city, depending on the size and
location of the advertisement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
