<HEADLINE> Africa Remains Most Landmine-Rich Continent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, February 17 (Xinhua) -- A U.S. landmine expert said
here today Africa is the most heavily mined continent with about
50 million uncleared landmines.
</P>
<P>
American Friends Service Committee's Southern Africa
representative John Stewart said that Angola is the worst
mine-affected country in the region with eight-to-20 million
uncleared landmines.
</P>
<P>
"Angola has one of the highest rates of landmine injuries per
capita in the world... An estimated 10,000 Angolans are landmine
disabled out of a population of 10 million," said Stewart.
</P>
<P>
Retired Colonel Martin Rupiya in the University of Zimbabwe
Center for Defence Studies said Zimbabwe has up to two million
landmines and it is very difficult to remove them.
</P>
<P>
The worst mine-hit regions in Zimbabwe are those communal
areas, mainly located along its border with Mozambique. enditem

