<HEADLINE> EU Clears Dutch Paper-maker's Buy Into Germany, Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, February 17 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU)
cleared today the Dutch paper and packaging company KNP BT's
acquisitions of two paper merchants in Germany and Italy.
</P>
<P>
The approval, by EU's executive arm, the European Commission,
cleared KNP BT's way to acquire the control of Wilhelm Seiler GmbH
of Germany and Bunzl Italia SpA of Italy.
</P>
<P>
Both Wilhelm Seiler GmbH and Bunzl Italia SpA are subsidiaries
of the Bunzl group headquartered in Britain.
</P>
<P>
The EU said KNP BT's increasing market shares in Italy and
Germany are unlikely to result in a dominant position there, since
other distributors and producers pose sufficient competition.
</P>
<P>
KNP BT is one of the leading producers of paper, board and
packaging, as well as a distributor of graphic paper and other
office products in Europe. 
</P>
