<HEADLINE> Yeltsin, Rodionov Discuss Military Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 17 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
and Defense Minister Igor Rodionov today discussed military
reform, a communique issued by the presidential press service said.
</P>
<P>
Their 40-minute meeting focused on orientations and contents of
a military reform, army funding, the social protection of
servicemen and members of their families.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin emphasised that although there were different
approaches and opinions about a military reform, a final decision
was to be made by himself, the head of state.
</P>
<P>
The reform will be further discussed at a Yeltsin-chaired
Defense Council session in March, the communique said.
</P>
<P>
Before today's meeting, Yeltsin denied a possible resignation
of Rodionov. 
