<HEADLINE> Argentine President Visits Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, February 17 (Xinhua) -- Argentina and Vietnam today
agreed to enhance their cooperation in various respects, the
Vietnamese News Agency (VNA) said in a report tonight.
</P>
<P>
The agreements were signed by visiting Argentine President
Carlos Menem and Vietnamese Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet during
their meeting here today.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreements, the two nations will cooperate in
agriculture, environment, science and technology.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, the two leaders shared the same view that the
visit will be an important landmark in the relationship between
Vietnam and Argentina and that the two countries enjoy favorable
conditions and potentials for closer cooperation for mutual
benefits.
</P>
<P>
They also exchanged views on global and regional issues of
common concerns and promised to work for peace, cooperation and
development in Southeast Asia, Latin America and other regions of
the world.
</P>
<P>
The General Secretary of the Communist Party of Vietnam Do Muoi
received Menem late today, who, at the invitation of Kiet, arrived
here late Sunday for an official visit on the first leg of his
Southeast Asian tour.
</P>
<P>
Muoi whished the two sides would find out cooperative ways
suitable for each country's strength, especially in the areas of
agriculture, livestock breeding, milk processing and labor
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Argentine president, accompanied by 50 Argentine
businessmen, will leave here for Bangkok tomorrow after
inaugurating the Argentine Embassy in Hanoi.
</P>
<P>
His visit is the first by a head of state of the South American
country since the two countries established diplomatic relations
in 1975. 
</P>
</TEXT>
