<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Tourism to Earn Near 300 Million US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE,February 17 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's tourism industry is
this year expected to earn the country 272 million US Dollars,
the Zimbabwe Tourism Authority (ZTA) said here today.
</P>
<P>
ZTA Chief Executive Joseph Chigwedere said there was an
expected growth of 10 percent in the sector and about 30 percent
growth in income.
</P>
<P>
However, he could not provide arrival figures as he said the
thrust of the ZTA was on revenue generated.
</P>
<P>
He added since 1980, Zimbabwe's tourist arrivals and receipts
had grown at an average annual rate of 10 percent and 30
percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
He told delegates at a one-day meeting on tourism in Harare
that as one of the strategies to promote the development of
the sector, the ZTA would host a tourism investment conference
later this year.
</P>
<P>
He urged local governments to take more responsibility in
tourism planning and development to ensure that the benefits
accrued to the local people through job creation, increased
incomes and infrastructural development. enditem

