<HEADLINE> Angola Sees Sharp Reduction in School Enrolment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, February 17 (Xinhua) -- The school enrolment rate in
Angola has reduced sharply in recent years, Education Minister
Burity Dasilva said in the central city of Kuito today when all
schools opened around the southern African country.
</P>
<P>
The reduction is due to the nearly 20-year-long civil war
which has destroyed a huge number of schools and the current poor
quantity and quality of teachers, Dasilva said.
</P>
<P>
He urged the church, the non-governmental groups, the
businessmen and all walks of the life to make efforts to
solve the education crisis which should be seen as a national
problem.
</P>
<P>
He called for the immediate improvement of teachers' working
and living conditions so as to attract people of ability to
devote themselves to education.
</P>
<P>
However, the promotion of education depends on sound political
development, the forming of a government of national unity and
reconciliation, as well as the implement of a set of political
and economic measures concerned, he said.
</P>
<P>
The free movement of people and cargos, better communication
facilities, the more favorable conditions in rural areas are also
needed to develop education, he noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
