<HEADLINE> Beijing Speeds Up State-owned Enterprise Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 18 (Xinhua) -- China's capital city Beijing
will speed up the reform of state-owned enterprises this year,
Beijing's Acting Mayor Jia Qinglin said during the ongoing session
of the municipal legislature.
</P>
<P>
The city plans to support key enterprises, concentrating its
efforts on large-sized firms and groups. Cooperation between these
firms is encouraged, Jia said.
</P>
<P>
Emphasis will be placed on the cooperation between industrial
giants such as the Beijing Chemical Group and the Yanshan
Petrochemical Corporation, he added.
</P>
<P>
Jia said that the city will experiment with the modern
enterprise system in 104 firms this year, and that a number of the
qualified companies will be re-organized into limited-liability
businesses.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the city will further improve the social security
system, and widen the coverage of unemployment insurance, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Jia said the the municipal government will further reform the
state enterprises through the separation of government
administration and enterprise operation. At the same time,
information consultation, technology and legal services will be
developed to speed up the reform.
</P>
<P>
He asked all the government departments to support the reform
work.  
</P>
</TEXT>
