<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Henan, Beijing Delay Opponents' Run to Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 18 (Xinhua/OANA) -- Beijing Lions and Henan
Wildcats delayed their rivals' run to the Chinese professional
basketball league finals by winning their second home matches at
the best-of-seven semi-finals on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Beijing, which had lost its first three matches, downed
Guangzhou Rams 108-99, while Henan, also trailing 0-3 going to
Tuesday's games, nipped Jilin Tigers 117-106.
</P>
<P>
Beijing, which took a 51-48 lead in the first half, extended
the margin to 85-74 in the end of the third quarter.
</P>
<P>
The host team jumped to 91-74 with a 6-0 run at the beginning
of the final quarter. Guangzhou clawed back tenaciously and put
up a 12-0 run to overtake Beijing 97-96 with four minutes to go.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou's momentum ended here. With many a defensive error
plus a low field goal percentage, Beijing posted a 12-2 run to
wrap up the mad-tempered match which saw several players expelled
for committing six fouls.
</P>
<P>
Henan jumped to a 30-21 lead in the first quarter, but Jilin
overtook the host 64-55 at the halftime as Henan's foreign
recruits were benched most of the second quarter.
</P>
<P>
With well-organized defence and aggressive attacks, Henan
turned the table at the third quarter to lead 87-84 and finally
took the match with a 11 points gap.
</P>
<P>
Beijing and Henan will play their third home matches on
Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
