<HEADLINE> Palestinian Leaders Call for Dialog Among </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Two Palestinian Leaders from
different political factions today called for a comprehensive
dialog between the eight PLO groups, including the extremist Hamas
and Jihad movements.
</P>
<P>
The call was jointly made by Mayef Hawatmeh, secretary general
of the Damascus-based Democratic Front for the Liberation of
Palestine (DFLP), and Farouq Kadoumi, Head of the Palestine
Liberation Organization Political Department, who is currently in
Damascus.
</P>
<P>
A DFLP statement quoted Hawatmeh and Kadoumi as underlining at
their meeting here the necessity of achieving Palestinian national
unity.
</P>
<P>
Without unity, they said, the Palestine Liberation Organization
(PLO) institutions would remain paralyzed, and it would be
impossible to halt Israeli settlement in Jerusalem, the West Bank
and Gaza Strip.
</P>
<P>
The two Palestinian leaders agreed "to make joint efforts to
conduct a genuine Palestinian national dialog."
</P>
<P>
They also vowed to jointly rebuild the PLO institutions for
unity, which is "the more powerful weapon in the hands of the
Palestinian people, especially on the eve of the
Palestinian-Israeli final status negotiations due to start on
March 17." 
</P>
