<HEADLINE> Shanghai Mayor Sees More Booming Foreign Trade This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Mayor Xu Kuangdi has
vowed to further expand the municipality's foreign trade, and
guarantee better product quality and higher efficiency in
foreign trade enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Addressing today's opening of the fifth annual session of the
Tenth Shanghai Municipal People's Congress, the municipal
legislature, Xu set the total import and export trade this year at
14.5 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The city's foreign trade has been expanding rapidly over the
past three years, with the total volume last year hitting 13.24
billion US dollars, an increase of 14.3 percent over 1995.
</P>
<P>
In particular, the city will continue to increase the export of
machinery and electronic products this year, he noted.
</P>
<P>
In addition, with 11.07 billion US dollars of contracted
foreign investment, overseas businessmen brought about 4.7 billion
US dollars to the city, and actual investment this year is
expected to reach 4.8 billion US dollars, the mayor said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
