<HEADLINE> Chinese Film Panorama Opens in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 18 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Film Panorama
'97 opened here today, the first time an ad hoc festival for the
mainland-produced films is organized in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Nan, director of the Xinhua News Agency Hong Kong Branch,
and Tung Chee Hwa, Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR), attended the opening ceremony this
evening.
</P>
<P>
A total of 15 films produced over the past three years will be
shown during the two-week festival, giving Hong Kong audience an
overall view of recent Chinese films.
</P>
<P>
An 18-member Chinese film delegation, composed of well-known
playwrights, directors, actors and actresses took part in the
gala.
</P>
<P>
They will exchange views with their Hong Kong counterparts at a
seminar entitled "An Overview of Recent Chinese Films".
</P>
<P>
Besides, a painting and calligraphy exhibition will be held
during the festival, which is scheduled for February 18 through
March 1.
</P>
<P>
The film festival is organized by the South China Film Industry
Workers Union and sponsored by the Hong Kong Urban Council.
