<HEADLINE> Beijing Selects Five Key Sectors for Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Beijing Acting Mayor Jia
Qinglin said today the economic growth in Beijing will be focused
on five selected sectors: the hi-tech, service trades, modern
agriculture, housing construction and pillar industries.
</P>
<P>
In a work report to the Municipal People's Congress, which
opened today, Jia said the development of the capital's hi-tech
sector will center on the information industry, biological
engineering and the exploration of new medicines.
</P>
<P>
This year, in addition to the further control over construction
of large shopping malls, Beijing will build a number of
neighborhood markets, supermarkets and chain stores in an effort
to benefit the entire public.
</P>
<P>
To promote the modern agricultural sector, Beijing will
establish 7,000 hectares of "model farmland" expected to offer
high yields, and will form a number of new agricultural group
companies this year.
</P>
<P>
Jia said that Beijing's gross domestic product last year
reached 160.7 billion yuan (20 billion US dollars), a 9.1 percent
rise over the previous year.  
</P>
