<HEADLINE> Famous Lake in Yunnan Province to Be Better Protected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, February 18 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese state councilor has
urged local officials in southwest China's Yunnan Province to take
steps to purify Dianchi Lake.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a meeting to discuss treating Dianchi Lake, Song
Jian said today that the water quality of Dianchi, one of the
leading scenic resort in Yunnan, must be markedly improved by May
of 1999, when an international gardening exposition will be held
in the province.
</P>
<P>
Song, also director of the Environmental Protection Committee
of the State Council, noted that the pollution in the lake has
become very serious, affecting the local ecological balance,
agricultural and industrial production, people's lives and tourism.
</P>
<P>
Song called on local officials to step up the treatment of
industrial waste and urban sewage, so that a complete biological
circle could be formed by the year 2010.  
