<HEADLINE> Forum on Deng Xiaoping's Economic Theories Held </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Zhu
Rongji today called for the study of Deng Xiaoping's economic
theories to boost the country's socialist modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Guided by the basic principles of Marxism, Deng has integrated
the conditions of China with the rest of the world through his
theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics, Zhu
said at a forum on Deng's economic theories.
</P>
<P>
The forum was sponsored by the Financial and Economic Leading
Group under the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Zhu, also member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, said Deng has put forward a
series of significant ideas, basic viewpoints and strategic
thought to add to the principles concerning China's socialist
economic development.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier noted that over the past two decades, China's
achievements in the process of reform, opening-up and
modernization have shown that Deng Xiaoping's economic theories
are scientific, have great vitality and should be taken as basic
guidelines for building the socialist system.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, two books on Deng's economic theories have been
published; the introduction to one was written by Chinese
President Jiang Zemin.  
</P>
