<HEADLINE> PLA General Staff Chief Meets Turkish Air Force Commander </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Fu Quanyou, Chief of the
General Staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA) met
with Turkey Commander of the Air Force Ahmet Gorekci here this
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Fu, Also member of the Central Military Commission, expressed
his belief that Gorekci's current visit to China would surely
further the existing friendship between the two armed forces,
especially the two air forces.
</P>
<P>
Fu said that the two armies have enjoyed close contact and
friendly cooperation, adding that China holds a positive attitude
toward furthering friendly relations, and hopes to enhance such
relations.
</P>
<P>
As of China's national defense policy and the situation of the
military building, Fu noted that China's national defense policy
is defensive, and China opposes hegemonism, power politics and
aggression of any form.
</P>
<P>
China never establish military alliance with other countries
nor station soldier or set up military base in other countries,
added Fu.
</P>
<P>
Fu said it is the mission of China's armed forces to safeguard
the integrity of the sovereignty and territory and provide solid
guarantee for the reform and opening up and the construction of
modernization.
</P>
<P>
Gorekci said Turkey and China have many similar situations,
expressing hopes to further increase exchanges and cooperations
between the two armies.
</P>
<P>
Gorekci arrived here on Monday as the guest of Liu Shunrao, PLA
commander of the air force. 
</P>
