<HEADLINE> Swedish King Visits South Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Swedish King Carl Gustaf and
Queen Silvia began their state visit to South Africa today.
</P>
<P>
The Swedish royal couple are scheduled to meet with South
African President Nelson Mandela at Tuynhuys, the president's
official residence in central Cape Town.
</P>
<P>
They will visit the Commission of Truth, where Nobel Peace
Prize winner Archbishop Desmond Tutu will be the host, and Robben
Island, where President Mandela was jailed for more than 27 years.
</P>
<P>
Other places the Swedish King and Queen will tour include the
University of Cape Town, hospitals and museums.
</P>
<P>
The royal couple are accompanied by Swedish Deputy Foreign
Minister Pierre Schori, who will sign a new agreement with
President Mandela today on Swedish aid to South Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
