<BODY>
<HEADLINE> State Budget for 1997 Passed in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, February 18 (Xinhua) -- A tightened budget for the
1997 financial year has been adopted here with its priority being
put for the achievement of peace and national reconciliation.
</P>
<P>
A communique issued by the Council of Ministers meeting late
last night said during the year, the government will raise the
living standards of the people by increasing supplies, hiking
wages and controlling inflation.
</P>
<P>
It did not disclose how much the state will spend this year.
But Finance Minister Alcantra Monteiro said last week that the
budget would be 617.6 billion revised Kwanza, or roughly 24.7
billion U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
It is a tightened budget, which will carry out strict
supervision over expenditures, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
The budget will attach importance to production and social
demands besides defense needs, it noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
