<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Schedules Large Treasury Bond Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 18 (Xinhua) -- China plans to issue 123
billion yuan (about 14.8 billion US dollars) in certificate bonds
between March 1 and October 20, the Ministry of Finance announced
today.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, 73 billion yuan will be in three-year bonds with
an annual coupon rate of 9.18 percent, 25 billion yuan in two-year
bonds with a yearly interest rate of 8.64 percent, and another 25
billion yuan in five-year bonds with an annual rate of 10.17
percent, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The bonds cannot be listed or traded at the stock market, the
ministry said. Individual investors can buy the bonds from the
country's four state-owned commercial banks -- the Industrial and
Commercial Bank, the Agricultural Bank of China, the China
Construction Bank and the Bank of China -- or from treasury-bond
operations affiliated with the financial departments.
</P>
<P>
The scheduled bond issue is China's second this year. Between
January 22 and February 17, China issued 20 billion yuan two-year
government bonds.
</P>
<P>
China's treasury bond issue has been growing rapidly in recent
years, to more than 195 billion yuan last year. This year's
treasury bond issue is expected to reach more than 250 billion
yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
