<HEADLINE> Regional Visa Board Meeting to be held in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, February 18 (Xinhua) -- A regional meeting of Visa
International is scheduled to open here tomorrow to discuss the
emerging credit card markets in central and east Europe, Middle
East and Africa region.
</P>
<P>
Expected to attend the two-day meeting are President and Chief
Executive of Visa International Edmund Jensen, and regional
President of the company Anne L. Cobb.
</P>
<P>
John Simba, Executive Chairman of the National Bank of Kenya,
is among the 18 directors drawn from some 13 countries in the
region.
</P>
<P>
After a restructuring, the Visa International is now divided
into six regions, that is, the U.S., Canada, Latin America, the
European Union, Asia and Pacific, and central and east Europe,
Middle East and Africa region.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest statistics, member banks and financial
institutions of the Visa International transact annual business
worth 643 billion U.S. Dollars using Visa cards and travelers
checks in 200 countries and territories.
</P>
<P>
In Kenya, the number of the banks issuing Visa credit cards
has increased in the past two years from one to five. They are
Barclays Bank of Kenya, Cooperative Bank of Kenya, Kenya
Commercial Bank, National Bank of Kenya and the Post Office
Savings Banks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
