<HEADLINE> S. Leone Gets 15m Dollars for Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FREETOWN, February 18 (Xinhua) - Tens of thousands of Sierra
Leone refugees will get a total of 15 million U.S. Dollars from
the World Bank for their resettlement and rehabilitation program,
a World Bank official told Xinhua here today.
</P>
<P>
Florian Fischel who is heading a World Bank mission to visit
this west African state, disclosed that his bank will assist in
designing and implementing the demobilization and resettlement
program for refugees and displaced persons in the country.
</P>
<P>
He was speaking in an interview with Xinhua after a meeting
with the eight member Commission for the Consolidation of Peace
(CCP) which is coordinating the peace process in Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
Fischel said he discussed with the commission members, which
includes four members of the Revolutionary United Front
combatants, "issues relating to disarmament and demobilization."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, an official from the U.N. High Commissioner for
Refugees (UNHCR) said here today that a total of 882 Sierra
Leonean refugees have now been brought to Freetown from Liberia.
</P>
<P>
Of these, 400 were transported in three vessels belonging to
the Sierra Leone Navy last Saturday, said the official, who added
that the rest were mainly old women and the pregnant. 
</P>
