<HEADLINE> China's Huaxia Bank Provides Round-the-Clock Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Huaxia Bank, headquartered in
Beijing, today became the first Chinese bank to provide 24-hour
service year round.
</P>
<P>
A bank official said that though some Chinese savings banks
have extended their hours into the night, Huaxia is the first to
stay open around the clock, all year.
</P>
<P>
He added that the services offered at night are the same as
during the day.
</P>
<P>
Established at the end of 1992, Huaxia has evolved into a
national commercial bank with 30 billion yuan (about 3.6 billion
US dollars) in total assets. It has set up branches in Beijing,
Hangzhou, Nanjing and Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
The official revealed that Huaxia will launch other new
services in the near future, but he declined to give more
details. 
</P>
</TEXT>
