<HEADLINE> Pak PM to Seek Vote of Confidence Wednesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif will seek vote of confidence from the National
Assembly Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The National Assembly will convene its first working session of
the parliament at 3 p.m. Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the Pakistan's Constitution, the prime minister
has to seek vote of confidence within a period of 60 days of his
assumption of office.
</P>
<P>
However, Sharif, who enjoys support of over two-thirds members
of the National Assembly, seemingly wants to fulfill this
constitutional formality in less than a week of his assumption of
office.
</P>
<P>
Sharif took oath Monday as the 13th prime minister of Pakistan
since 1947.  
