<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, February 18 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading French newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- The Algerian national carrier, Air Algeria, will resume its
direct flight from Algiers to Paris on April 1, after a two-year
suspension.
</P>
<P>
Air Algeria stopped flying to Paris in 1995 after France asked
it to transfer its charter terminal from Orly-Sud airport to
Roissy airport for security reasons.
</P>
<P>
-- The Zairean Defense Ministry confirmed Monday evening that
Zairean air force bombed earlier in the day several towns in
eastern Zaire which are controlled by the Tutsi-led rebels.
</P>
<P>
International humanitarian groups estimated that the bombing
killed six to nine people and wounded dozens of others.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- The Basque separatist group ETA launched its fourth deadly
bombing attack within one week on Monday in Bilbao, Spain, in
which one policeman was killed in a car bomb explosion.
</P>
<P>
The Spanish Interior Ministry said that although French police
have been cooperating in cracking down on ETA members, some top
leaders of the group have always been hiding somewhere in France.
</P>
<P>
-- Israeli Prime Minister Benyamin Netanyahu was met with a
tempest of fury from his Likud party members when he returned home
on Monday from a four-day visit in Washington.
</P>
<P>
His partisans suspected him of having promised U.S. President
Bill Clinton to suspend the construction of 6,500 housing units in
a new Jewish settlement in East Jerusalem. 
