<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Anti-Corruption Clinics Planned In Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania Presidential
Commission on Corruption plans to hold anti-corruption clinics
with implementers and members of the public to make the
anti-corruption campaign more effective.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed here on Monday by the commision's
secretary, Mr. Alex Muganda in his presentation on the findings
of the commission at a one-week workshop on investigative
journalism for female journalists.
</P>
<P>
The secretary said the clinics would focus on education and
awareness creation on corruption among members of public. He said
people would be educated on their rights, why they should say
'no' to corruption and where to submit complaints.
</P>
<P>
Mr. Muganda further explained that in a report to President
Mkapa last December, the commission reported that corrupt
practices were rampant from top leadership positions to the
bottom and suggested remedies to the problem.
</P>
<P>
Mr. Muganda said although a number of people were mentioned in
the report no legal action has been taken against them so far
allegedly because law enforcers were still investigating the
allegations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
