<HEADLINE> Mourning Named NBA Player of the Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, February 17 (Xinhua) -- Alonzo Mourning of the Miami
Heat edged Vancouver's Bryant Reeves Monday for NBA Player of the
Week honors for games played from February 10 through 16.
</P>
<P>
Mourning led Miami to a 3-0 record by averaging 27.3 points,
11.3 rebounds and 4.0 blocked shots per game, while shooting .763
(29-for-38) from the field.
</P>
<P>
He ranked second in field goal percentage, third in scoring and
blocked shots and tied for ninth in rebounding among
league-leaders for the week.
</P>
<P>
"Alonzo's play has been solid for us," said Miami head coach
Pat Riley, following the Heat's 106-90 win against Indiana on
February 13. "He's going hard to the hoop and he's using his jump
hook effectively."
</P>
<P>
Miami (39-12), which has won nine consecutive games and seven
in a row at home, leads the Atlantic Ocean Division by two games
over the New York Knicks (37-14). The heat is off to its best
start in franchise history and is 16 games better than at this
same point last season (23-28).
</P>
<P>
Mourning had a team-high 29 points, 11 rebounds and five
blocked shots in 37 minutes played in a 104-91 win against Detroit
on February 11. He shot .714 (10-for-14) from the field.
</P>
<P>
The fifth-year pro from Georgetown University improved on his
sparking shooting by converting 9-of-10 field goals and tallying a
team-high 29 points, 13 rebounds and three blocked shots in the
victory against Indiana on February 13.
</P>
<P>
Mourning closed out the week with 24 points (10-for-14), 10
rebounds and four blocked shots in a 125-99 win over Philadelphia.
</P>
<P>
Reeves helped lead Vancourver to a 2-1 record by averaging 27.0
points, 11.3 rebounds and 1.7 assists per game. He shot .682
(30-for-44) from the field and .808 (21-for-26) from the free
throw line and ranked fourth in scoring, eighth in field goal
percentage and tied for ninth in rebounding among league-leaders
for the week. 
</P>
