<HEADLINE> Birth Rate Up in Germany in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, February 18 (Xinhua) -- The number of babies born in
Germany in 1996 rose for the first time since German unification
in 1990, which totalled 789,000, or a 3.8-percent increase over
1995, according to official data today.
</P>
<P>
In eastern Germany, the number of births surged 11.5 percent to
92,000, while in western Germany it rose by 2.9 percent to 697,000.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the nation's number of deaths last year increased by
0.4 percent to 879,000 out of a population of about 80 million.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that the number of marriages dropped by 0.7
percent to 426,500 in 1996, with a 0.2 percent fall registered in
the eastern part and a 0.8 percent in the western part. 
