<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uganda to Double Coffee Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Uganda Coffee Farmers'
Association (UCFA) has decided to double the country's current
annual coffee production of four million bags (60 kg per bag)
during the next five years.
</P>
<P>
According to a local daily "the new vision" today, a five-year
plan (1996-2001) released on Saturday said UCFA would also strive
for improving the quality of coffee, the number one foreign
exchange earner in Uganda, apart from increasing its yield.
</P>
<P>
As part of the effort to boost the production, UCFA will
directly export at least 30 percent of coffee products into some
special markets and an extension service will be established in
all major coffee-growing sub-counties with all their activities
fully financed by the farmers.
</P>
<P>
The association will also develop an efficient and functional
information system and encourage the farmers to use
environment-friendly farming methods such as using proper and
sustainable methods of soil management. 
</P>
</TEXT>
