<HEADLINE> Malaysia, Singapore to Hold Air Defense Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia will hold a
combined air defense exercise with Singapore over Peninsular
Malaysia and Singapore tomorrow under the Five-Power Defense
Arrangement (FPDA), according to the Malaysian news agency Bernama
today.
</P>
<P>
The one-day exercise, codenamed Minor ADEX 97/1, will be
coordinated by the Headquarters Integrated Air Defense System,
located at the Royal Malaysian Air Force (RMAF) base in
Butterworth, Pulau Pinang, and under the command of Air Vice
Marshall Errol John McCormack, it said.
</P>
<P>
RMAF's aircraft to be involved in the exercise are the Mig 29N,
Hawk, KC-130, MB339, Beechcraft B200T and Cessna 402B, while the
Republic of Singapore Air Force (RSAF) will take part with F-5E
Tigers, F-16 Fighting Falcons, A4-SU Super Skyhawks, C-130
Hercules, Fokker 50 and the UH-1H, Super Puma and Fennec
helicopters, according to the Malaysian news agency.
</P>
<P>
Aircraft of the RMAF and The RSAF will act both as defenders
and aggressors during the exercise.  
</P>
</TEXT>
