<HEADLINE> Mcdonald's Opens Outlet in Thai Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Mcdonald's Thailand has opened
an outlet in a Bangkok hospital, becoming the first fast-food
restaurant to open in a hospital in Thailand.
</P>
<P>
In the highly competitive fast-food market, Mcdonald's is
planning to open more "non-traditional" outlets in places such as
schools, office buildings, shopping malls and hospitals.
</P>
<P>
In Thailand, caterers run restaurants at public places such as
those above-mentioned, even in government ministry compounds,
selling fast Thai food, such as rice flour noodles.
</P>
<P>
Mcdonald's Thailand added 30 percent more outlets last year and
now operates 53 restaurants in Bangkok, Pattaya, Chiang Mai and
Phuket.
</P>
<P>
Beside setting up more outlets, the U.S.-patented fast-food
chain has also moved further towards its standardization program,
resulting in all outlets carrying the same format of menu,
material purchases at selected points, and more streamlined
marketing activities.  
</P>
