<HEADLINE> Olympic Swimming Star Misses Doping Test </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 17 (Xinhua) -- Irland's triple Olympic
champion Michelle Smith has missed an out-of-competition doping
test and could be banned if she misses another, the world
governing body of the sport said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The International Swimming Federation (FINA) told the Associate
Press that Smith was absent when the FINA drug testers arrived at
her home in Ireland last October.
</P>
<P>
But FINA said Smith's absence did not mean she had violated any
FINA rules right now.
</P>
<P>
According to relevant doping rules, a swimmer would face a
four-year ban, which is decided by a independent doping panel, if
he or she misses two such doping tests.
</P>
<P>
At the Atlanta Olympic Games, Smith won the 400 meters
freestyle, 200 meters individual medley and 400 meters individual
medley. She also took bronze in the 200 meters butterfly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
