<HEADLINE> East China City Witnesses Rapid Development Of Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WEIHAI, February 18 (Xinhua) -- East China's port city of
Weihai approved 2,143 foreign-funded projects last year, with the
contractual overseas investment reaching 530 million US dollars,
according to the latest statistics.
</P>
<P>
Figures show that the city has been taking the lead in Shandong
Province in the overall development of foreign trade, with the
trade volume exceeding 2.1 billion dollars-worth in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The city signed 123 overseas project and labor export contracts
with a total value of more than 37 million dollars in the same
year.
</P>
<P>
The trade volume of the city's 650 enterprises engaged in
processing trade reached 1.12 billion dollars in 1996, and the
19 foreign-funded enterprises raked in some 10 million dollars
each.
</P>
<P>
Weihai last year reported marked increases in the ratio of
products with high added value to the export of manufactured
goods, which accounted for more than 80 percent of the total
exported goods.
</P>
<P>
With the improvement of the investment environment, the city
has attracted many high-level overseas projects. Since last year,
many well-known large corporations from Japan, the Republic of
Korea and Britain have come to invest in the city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
