<HEADLINE> East China Province Improving Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, February 18 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang
province recently developed new plans to improve its urban and
rural environment.
</P>
<P>
The plans call for 100 cement plants and 100 major pollution
sources to be given priority in the clean-up, and 100 ecological
villages or towns to be established this year.
</P>
<P>
Sources of pollution in the Qiantang River Basin and the plains
stretching between the cities of Huang Yan, Jiao Jiang, and Wen
Zhou, are to be dealt with, and the province will bring air
pollution under control by establishing smoke and dust control
areas in all cities and towns.
</P>
<P>
Two regulations on radium pollution treatment and environmental
supervision and controls will be mapped out in the province, to
give legal muscle to local environmental work.
</P>
<P>
Provincial source said in the past year achievements in local
pollution treatment and ecological protection had been made, and
that some small plants that were seriously polluting were closed
down.  
</P>
