<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Shenyin &AMP; Wanguo Company Tops Annual Trading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 18 (Xinhua) -- The year-old Shenyin &AMP; Wanguo
Securities Co., Ltd topped all other Chinese securities firms in
annual trading on the Shanghai exchange last year, according to
today's Shanghai Securities News.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the Shanghai Stock Exchange show that
Shenyin &AMP; Wanguo, a merger of Shenyin Securities Co. Ltd and
Shanghai International Securities Co. Ltd, which were two of
China's largest securities firms, reported a combined turnover of
526.4 billion yuan (about 63.4 billion US dollars) in stocks,
funds and treasury bonds in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The second and third places in trading went to China Securities
Co. Ltd and the Trust and Investment Company of China Construction
Bank, with a volume of 334.1 billion yuan and 179.7 billion yuan,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
An analysis shows that the position of securities companies was
determined to a large extent by their treasury bond business.
</P>
<P>
All three had a government bond repurchase volume of more than
100 billion yuan. Shenyin and Wanguo's volume was 203.3 billion
yuan, and they reported the largest volume in spot trading of
treasury bonds, at 178.6 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Shenyin &AMP; Wanguo's trade in class-A shares, which are reserved
for domestic investors only, reached more than 122.5 billion yuan,
followed by 70.6 billion yuan for Haitong Securities Co. Ltd, and
62.3 billion yuan for China Securities Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Shenyin &AMP; Wanguo's fund transactions came to 7.9 billion yuan
last year, the largest at the Shanghai market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
