<HEADLINE> Dhaka Okays Formation of National Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, February 18 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi cabinet Monday
approved a proposal for setting up the National Stock Exchange
(NSE) in a bid to expand and streamline the country's capital
market.
</P>
<P>
With the formation of the NSE, the number of bourses in
Bangladesh will be three. The two other bourses are Dhaka Stock
Exchange and Chittagong Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
Chaired by Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina, the meeting accepted
the outlines of the proposed NSE, which will be a joint-venture by
the government and the private sector, according to official
sources.
</P>
<P>
The NSE would have corporate membership. It will also have
representatives from financial institutions, including
nationalized commercial banks and private banks.
</P>
<P>
However, the NSE is still in a conceptual stage. A detailed
feasibility study will be commissioned soon, the sources added.
</P>
