<HEADLINE> Record Number of Overseas New Year Phone Calls In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 18 (Xinhua) -- International phone calls in
Shanghai to relatives or friends overseas hit a record number
during the traditional Chinese New Year.
</P>
<P>
According to an official with the Shanghai Long-Distance
Exchange, on the eve of Spring Festival, Shanghai people made
20,021 direct international calls, 73.19 percent more than the
previous Spring Festival eve.
</P>
<P>
When added to the 68,908 international calls made through
long-distance call exchanges, an average of 246 phone calls were
made every minute during a six-hour period.
</P>
<P>
Calls to Hong Kong, Macao, and Taiwan had an increase of over
80 percent over the previous Spring Festival, and international
phone calls to Shanghai numbered more than 210,000, an average of
586 per minute during the peak period.
</P>
<P>
Spring Festival is the most important festival for the Chinese,
when they wish family members and friends a happy new year and
good luck in the coming year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
