<HEADLINE> Dhaka Industrial Zone Area to Be Expanded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Work on expansion of the Dhaka
Export Processing Zone (DEPZ) has been progressing fast to make
the area nearly double and accommodate more industrial units,
according to a press release of the Bangladesh Export Processing
Zones Authority.
</P>
<P>
The expanded area, covering 214 acres of land being developed
at a cost of about 600 million taka (15 million U.S. dollars),
will be commissioned by the middle of this year.
</P>
<P>
The new area of DEPZ will have more than 250 fully developed
industrial plots each of 2,000 square meters. These plots will be
ready for immediate commissioning of industries with gas, power,
water and telecommunications facilities.
</P>
<P>
With the expansion of DEPZ, the total area of this country's
second largest industrial zone will rise to 355 acres, said the
press release.
</P>
<P>
A total of 58 industries have been so far sanctioned for DEPZ
with a proposed investment of about 406.4 million dollars. These
industries will create employment opportunities for more than
37,000 Bangladeshi workers.
</P>
<P>
At present, about 15,000 workers are working in the 23
industries, which are in operation in the DEPZ with an investment
of 56.66 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The countries which have invested in DEPZ include South Korea,
Malaysia, China, Japan and Germany.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
