<HEADLINE> Contracts on Three Gorges projects Total 13 Billion Yuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Over 2,200 contracts have been
signed for the Three Gorges Dam Projects through public bidding in
the past four years, involving a combined contractual value of 13
billion yuan (about 1.5 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The agreements covered engineering, equipment purchase and
project management supervision, said an official in charge of the
Three Gorges project, located in central China and believed to be
the largest of its kind in the world.
</P>
<P>
Almost all the contracts on engineering and management
supervision were secured by Chinese construction firms and
project design institutes, while overseas firms won bids for most
of the equipment purchases.
</P>
<P>
In the past four years, more than 178 million cubic meters of
earth and stone have been dug and 3.4 million cubic meters of
concrete have been poured, and three billion yuan-worth of
equipment has been purchased, the official said.
</P>
<P>
This year will see an upsurge of competitive bidding, including
the bids for the main dam and the power house, which will require
a tremendous amount of work.
</P>
<P>
The bidding will be open in June.  
</P>
</TEXT>
