<DOCNO> XIE19970218.0209 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OPEC Price Down, Production Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, February 17 (Xinhua) -- The average price for OPEC's
basket of seven crudes went down to 20.57 U.S. dollars a barrel
last week, the Vienna-based OPEC Secretariat announced today.
</P>
<P>
Last week's average price dropped by 1.5 dollars compared with
the previous week's average price of 22.07 dollars a barrel,
falling below OPEC's reference oil price of 21 dollars a barrel
the first time in recent years.
</P>
<P>
OPEC's monthly average oil price in January was 23.19 dollars a
barrel, 32 cents down from the previous month's average price of
23.51 dollars a barrel.
</P>
<P>
The daily output of crude oil production of the 11 member
countries of OPEC reached 26.55 million barrels, rising above the
highest line of 25.03 million barrels set by the organization.
</P>
<P>
Iraq's return to the international oil market under the United
Nation's "oil for food" resolution was the main reason for the
increase in the crude oil production.
</P>
<P>
Iraq's daily crude oil production reached 3.7 million barrels
in January, of which 1.1 million barrels were exported. It was an
increase of 300,000 barrels compared with last December. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
