work in Ukraine, an EBRD official told Ukrainian Prime Minister
Pavel Lazarenko here today.
</P>
<P>
A delegation from the bank is on a one-week visit to Ukraine to
study the country's domestic situation, including consumer demand,
economic reform and privatization before coming up with a
detailed strategy.
</P>
