much from the EBRD and said that the bank could not provide all
the investment the country needs.
</P>
<P>
Lazarenko said he hoped the EBRD would increase its investment
in key sectors of the economy such as energy, urban transport,
infrastructure and aviation.
</P>
<P>
Roman Shpek, Director of the EBRD's bureau in Ukraine, said
after the meeting that the bank is studying 21 projects here with
a view to providing loans.
</P>
<P>
During the next two months, EBRD is expected to give Ukraine
the first batch of loans totaling 277 million dollars. 
