<HEADLINE> Alert Command Starts Operating in Jakarta </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKAARTA, February 18 (Xinhua) -- The Jakarta military command
on Monday began operating the national alert command (PKN) which
would be effective throughout the territory, military sources in
the Indonesian capital said today.
</P>
<P>
"Through the command post, people can contribute information to
the authority and related-agencies regarding the truth of rumors,"
Jakarta military chief Maj. Gen. Sutiyoso said.
</P>
<P>
Following recent rioting, President Soeharto has asked for
alert command posts to be set up at regional military commands
aimed at ensuring peace before the May general elections in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The task of the national alert post is to anticipate and early
detect various potential problems which may lead to mass riots and
disruption to the development process, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Sutiyoso said people were expected to give contribution to the
post because averting riots which may disrupt process of national
development was the responsibility of all Indonesian people.
</P>
<P>
The national alert command involved a number of parties,
including public figures, religious leaders, military, policemen
and the local municipal officers.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia has since last July been hit by a series of riots in
Jakarta, east Java, west Java and west Kalimantan during which 12
people were killed and scores injured and hundreds of public
buildings, shops and houses were destroyed.
</P>
<P>
however, government officials have said recently that despite
current riots in the country, political stability and security
were under control. 
</P>
</TEXT>
