<HEADLINE> Mountain Fire Quenched in Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, February 17 (Xinhua) -- A serious mountain fire which
flared up two days ago in Liguria, a region in northwest Italy,
was near to extinguishment today.
</P>
<P>
The fire, fanned by strong wind, spread to a large area and
affected three of the four provinces in the region, destroying
thousands of hectares of forest.
</P>
<P>
A large number of fire-fighters, with machinery including three
aircraft and eight helicopters, were mobilized to quench the
flames. 
</P>
