<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan President Vows to Bring Killers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan President Chandrika
Kumaratunga has vowed to bring the killers of District Member of
Parliamentarian Nalanda Ellawala to justice, according to official
sources here today.
</P>
<P>
Ellawala was killed last Tuesday at Kuruwita Town during
political clashes between the ruling People's Alliance (PA) and
the main Opposition United National Party (UNP).
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a public rally in Kalutara, over 50 kilometers from
Colombo, the president said that she will enact tough new laws to
impose the harshest penalties on the murderers and to disarm all
politicians, according to official sources here today.
</P>
<P>
She also said that she will disarm all politicians and allow
them only the two weapons they are legally entitled to posses.
</P>
<P>
She charged that the main opposition United National Party
(UNP) leadership was well aware of the criminal tendencies of some
politicians.
</P>
<P>
Because the UNP was aware that the Peoples Alliance would win
the forthcoming local government elections, they were now
resorting to violence.
</P>
<P>
She said her government was a democratic one which respected
law and order. And it was taking action against those who engage
in acts of terror. It was determined to wipe out terrorism the
country.  
</P>
