<HEADLINE> Acting President Names Ecuadoran Ministers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, February 17 (Xinhua) -- Ecuador's Acting President
Fabian Alarcon has named two more ministers for his cabinet.
</P>
<P>
The two are Minister of Energy and Mines Raul Baca Carbo, and
Secretary for Public Administration Arturo Gangotena.
</P>
<P>
Alarcon was selected by Congress as the country's interim
president early last week after the legislators voted to oust
President Abdala Bucaram on the grounds of "mental incompetence."
</P>
<P>
The 50-year-old congress leader will govern the country until
1998 when he is supposed to call new elections.
</P>
<P>
Alarcon appointed Thursday new cabinet ministers for defense,
finance, health and public works, in addition to the presidential
secretary named earlier.
</P>
<P>
Government sources said that Jose Ayala Lasso, Ecuador's senior
official at the United Nations on human rights, would probably be
named the new foreign minister.
</P>
<P>
Diego Ponce and a woman, whose name was yet to be revealed,
would be in charge of the Housing and Urban Development Ministry
and the Environment Ministry respectively.
</P>
<P>
Still to be designated are the ministers of industry and trade,
labor and human resources, information and tourism and social
welfare, for which there are still no nominations, the sources
said.
</P>
<P>
Alarcon also named Fidel Jaramillo manager of the Central Bank,
and Danilo Carrera chairman of the monetary board. 
