<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, February 17 (Xinhua) -- Fifth-seeded Felix Mantilla
of Spain downed Bernd Karbacher of Germany in the straight sets
6-2, 6-1 at the European Community Championship Monday in Antwerp,
Belgium.
</P>
<P>
The first round matches also saw Martin Damm of Germany was
defeated by Martin Sinner of the Czech Republic 6-7 (5-7), 6-4,
6-3.
</P>
<P>
Another Czech was less lucky as Bohdan Ulihrach withdrew after
trailing 5-2 in the opening set against local favorite Dick Norman
because of injury.
</P>
<P>
Mikael Tillstrom of Sweden beat Hernan Gumy of Argentina 4-6,
6-1, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Michael Stich will start to defend his ECC title against fellow
German Marc Goellner. Top-seeded Goran Ivanisevic of Croatia
starts against France's Guy Forget. 
</P>
</TEXT>
