<HEADLINE> Ecuador Boosts Banana Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, February 17 (Xinhua) -- Ecuadoran banana exports in
January this year increased approximately 19 percent compared with
the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
According to a report by the National Banana Program, this
Andean country exported 378,168 metric tons of bananas in January
1997, compared with the 319,082 metric tons exported in January
1996 -- an increase of 59.086 metric tons.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador earned about 112.5 million U.S. dollars last January
from banana exports, compared with 79 million dollars in January
1996.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador in January sold bananas mostly to the European Union,
the United States and China. 
