<HEADLINE> Oldest Woman in Cuba Dies at Age 114 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, February 17 (Xinhua) -- Elisa Robles Tomas, the oldest
woman in Cuba, died on February 6, a day after her 114th birthday
in the province of Holguin, said the weekly Cuban "Trabajadores"
(Workers) published today.
</P>
<P>
She left more than 200 descendents including great-great-great
grandchildren.
</P>
<P>
But her death was not known until a few days ago, the weekly
said.
</P>
<P>
The woman was born of Chinese and Haitian parents on February
5, 1883 in the municipality of Sagua de Tanamo of the country.
</P>
<P>
She said she had seen Major General Jose Maceo, an important
historical figure in Cuba's Independence War which started at the
end of the last century. 
</P>
