<HEADLINE> GCC-EU Ministerial Meeting Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, February 17 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Ministers of the
Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) and European Union (EU) today
ended their meeting in the Qatari capital of Doha, according to
reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
During the one-day meeting, the ministers reviewed "positive
achievements" made by the two blocs in the field of their
political and economic cooperation in the past year and discussed
ways of bolstering commercial ties between them, the Qatari News
Agency quoted a statement issued after the meeting as saying.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed matters of common concern, including the
peace process in the Middle East, NATO's peace-keeping mandate in
Bosnia, U.N. sanctions against Iraq and relations between Iraq
and GCC states.
</P>
<P>
The GCC groups Kuwait, Oman, Saudi Arabia, the United Arab
Emirates, Qatar and Bahrain. 
</P>
