<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Enjoys Best Investment Climate in Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, February 17 (Xinhua) -- The investment climate in
Zimbabwe now is the best in Africa thanks to a series of economic
liberalization measures taken by the government, the state-run
Zimbabwe Investment Center (ZIC) said today.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the southern African country currently is among
the leading contenders for investment in the world, ZIC said in
its latest publication.
</P>
<P>
ZIC said it approved in 1996 projects worth over 950 million
U.S. Dollars and with the potential of creating more than 12,000
jobs over a five-year period.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investment missions carried out in the past few years
have demonstrated the success of government efforts on economic
reforms, ZIC claimed. enditem

