<HEADLINE> Workshop on Establishing University Opens in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, February 17 (Xinhua) -- A workshop on
establishing the Africcan Virtual University (AVU), a
satelite-based high-level education network, was opened here
today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the workshop, Edward Jaycox, World Bank's retired
Vice-President and Senior Adviseor to the World Bank president,
said the AVU project enjoys tremendous support from the World
Bank, satelite communication companies who offered their service
and other international organizations.
</P>
<P>
Private corporations and foundations as well as educational
institutions worldwide have also expressed interest in the
project, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the task of making the project a truely African operation
rests on the Africans themselves. ''We must have a clearly
articulated approach to promote the development of content
by African academics. This is a prerequisite for and the most
tangible way to make the AVU an African operation,'' he added.
</P>
<P>
According to the organizers of the workshop, the AVU holds
immense potential, by producing engineers, scientists and business
managers that will help the continent keep pace with developments
in teh 21st centruy.
</P>
<P>
More than 70 university officials and academics from around
Africa are attending the five-day workshopm enditem

