<HEADLINE> African Insurance Firms Gather in Cameroun </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, February 17 (Xinhua) -- The 21th General Assembly
of the Federation of African National Insurance Companies
(FANAF) opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Camerounian Prime Minister Peter Mafani Musonge presided over
the open ceremony of the meeting.
</P>
<P>
He said Cameroun will support the insurance industry.
</P>
<P>
The FANAF guiding principles are professionalism and
solidarity, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was expected to focus on the impacts of the
economic globalization and the inter-African regional
insurance code on Africa's insurance sector.
</P>
<P>
About 300 experts from 20 African and European countries
are attending the meeting, which will close on February 20.
</P>
<P>
FANAF, founded in the 1970s, consists of 17 French-speaking
countries. Its last general assembly was held in
Yamoussoukro, Cote d'Ivoire in 1996. enditem


