<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Considers to Establish Road Fund </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, February 17 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian parliament,
the House of People's Representatives, discussed a draft bill on
the establishment of a road fund today, the Ethiopian News Agency
has reported.
</P>
<P>
Under the bill, the road fund will be collected from budget,
fuel levy, annual vehicle licence renewal fee based on axle load,
overloading fines and other road tariffs and used to timely
finance the road maintenance and road safety measures.
</P>
<P>
The bill demands the Ethiopian government allot 30 percent of
its capital budget to the development, maintenance and
rehabilitation of roads.
</P>
<P>
It means the government should spend 600 million Birr (about 92
million U.S. Dollars) per annum in the next five years.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian road authority said there are some 17,769
kilometers of roads in the country under its administration while
8,043 kilometers of roads under regional control and 3,000
kilometers managed at municipality-level. enditem

