<HEADLINE> S. Africa to Purchase 12 Rooivalk Helicopters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, February 17 (Xinhua) -- The South African Air
Force (SAAF) is considering buying 12 Rooivalk combat helicopters
from Denel, a leading arms manufacturer in the country, said a
source here today.
</P>
<P>
The first Rooivalk plane equipped with Mokopa anti-tank
missiles was expected to be delivered to the SAAF next year, said
the source.
</P>
<P>
Defence Minister Joe Modise said it is important for SAAF to
possess the best possible equipment to fulfill its diverse duties
in the maintenance of peace and the transport of humanitarian
aid.
</P>
<P>
The purchase of the Rooivalk by the SAAF could also create more
jobs, he said
</P>
<P>
Speaking after a public showing of the latest model of the
combat helicopters here, Denel Managing Director Johan Alberts said
the deal could generate 6,000 jobs for the country.
</P>
<P>
Denel is currently undertaking marketing exercises in the Far
East, the Middle East and Malaysia which has already expressed
particular interests in ordering the Rooivalk.
</P>
<P>
Denel Chairman Dave Brink said the Rooivalk, cheaper than the
U.S. Apache helicopter, represents the leading edge technology
for which South Africa holds the design authority. enditem

