<HEADLINE> Mubarak, Arafat Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, February 17 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
and Palestinian President Yasser Arafat, who arrived today, held
talks his evening at the Presidential headquarters here.
</P>
<P>
The talks cover the latest developments of the Mideast peace
process, particularly the Palestinian-Israeli track following the
implementation of the Palestinian-Israeli protocol on Israeli
withdrawal from the West Bank town of Hebron, the Egyptian
MENA news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Under the Hebron agreement signed last month, the Israelis and
Palestinians will begin talks on a final peace agreement within
two months. They will negotiate their final borders and the future
of Jerusalem and of the 144 Jewish settlements in the West Bank
and Gaza Strip.
</P>
<P>
Israeli and Palestinian negotiators will break into nine groups
from today to deal with pending issues in the Hebron protocol and
the interim agreement as a result of Sunday's peace talks between
Israeli and Palestinian negotiators, the first since the Hebron
agreement.
</P>
<P>
Arafat has said that the coming steps toward settling the
Palestinian issue depend on how the joint committees will work.
</P>
</TEXT>
