<HEADLINE> S.African Jailed in Iran Released </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, February 17 (Xinhua) -- A 27-year-old South
African has been freed and is soon to return home after being
jailed in a prison in Iran's capital Teheran for almost five
weeks, sources here said today.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman for the Department of the Foreign Affairs Marco Boni
said in Pretoria that the released, identified as Stuart Timm of
Johannesburg, now is staying at the home of South African
Ambassador to Iran Moosa Moolla in Teheran.
</P>
<P>
Timm had been held without charges since January 12 when he
was arrested with a Swiss companion during a tour to Iran to buy
leather. He then was working on a social program in neighboring
Turkmenistan.
</P>
<P>
South Africa has since then made several attempts through
diplomatic channels to get Timm released, but in vain.
</P>
<P>
A strong protest was lodged to the Iranian authorities about
two weeks ago and Foreign Minister Alfred Nzo also urged Teheran
to either charge or release Timm.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Ambassador to South Africa Mohammed Mahdavi last week
reportedly returned to Teheran to expedite Timm's release.
</P>
<P>
Boni said Nzo was informed on Sunday by his Iranian counterpart Ali
Ahkbar Velayati that Timm would be released today.
</P>
<P>
"We are extremely pleased that the matter has been resolved," said
Boni. enditem

