<HEADLINE> EU Condemns Interference in Conflict in Eastern Zaire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, February 17 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) today
"strongly" condemned all interference in the conflict in Zaire and
called for the withdrawal of all outside and mercenary forces.
</P>
<P>
A declaration issued by the EU presidency said that the EU was
"greatly concerned" at the military build-up in the east of Zaire.
</P>
<P>
It might aggravate the political problems and widen the
humanitarian crisis in the region, the document said.
</P>
<P>
The EU called on the parties to the conflict to negotiate a
cease-fire without delay and to facilitate access to the region
for humanitarian organizations.
</P>
<P>
It reaffirmed its support for the early holding of an
international conference on peace, security and stability in the
Great Lakes region under the aegis of the United Nations and the
Organization of African Unity.
</P>
<P>
The EU also said it was prepared to implement substantial aid
for economic and social rehabilitation at regional level as soon
as political circumstances and the security situation so permit.
</P>
</TEXT>
