<HEADLINE> Turkish Parliament to Approve Plan to Send Troops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, February 17 (Xinhua) -- The Turkish parliament is to
approve this week the resolution made by the government to send
Turkish troops to Hebron as part of the international force
monitoring the handover of the West Bank town.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish cabinet agreed to send 17 soldiers to Hebron last
week.
</P>
<P>
In view of the fact, the parliament is believed to give the
green light to Turkey's overseas military mission.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish constitution stipulates that to send troops abroad
is subject to ratification by the parliament.
</P>
<P>
Troops from Denmark, Italy, Sweden, Switzerland, Norway and
Turkey have been invited to supervise the Israeli handover of
Hebron to the PNA.
</P>
<P>
PNA President Yasser Arafat, who is to pay a one-day official
visit to Turkey Thursday, has said that the Turkish presence in
Hebron is welcomed.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Foreign Ministry Spokesman Omer Akbel told reporters
today that Arafat will discuss the dispatch of Turkish soldiers
to Hebron with Turkish leaders during his visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
