<HEADLINE> German Leaders Praise King Hussein's Good Offices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, February 17 (Xinhua) -- German Chancellor Helmut Kohl and
Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel today praised the role of King
Hussein of Jordan in helping to bring about the Hebron agreement
between the Paletinians and Israel.
</P>
<P>
King Hussein held talks with Kohl and Kinkel in Bonn today, the
first day of his two-day visit to Germany.
</P>
<P>
According to German government spokesman Peter Hausmann, Kohl
and Hussein agreed in their talks that the Middle East peace
process should proceed constructively "in the spirit of mutual
trust and for the benefit of those affected."
</P>
<P>
King Hussein also met with Germany's Economic Cooperation and
Development Minister Carl-Dieter Spranger today.
</P>
<P>
Spranger told Hussein that Germany would continue to support
Jordan's development. Planned programs include provision of
drinking water and vocational trainings. 
